Explanation:
We use dynamic programming to solve the problem by creating a 2D array dp[] with dimensions n x n, where n is the length of the input string s. We iterate through the string from left to right and update dp[i] based on the substrings before and after index i. If the characters at indices i and i+1 are 'A' and 'B', update dp[i] to be the minimum of dp[i-1] and dp[i+1]. If the characters at indices i and i+1 are 'A' and 'C', update dp[i] to be the minimum of dp[i-1] and dp[i+1].

Finally, return the value stored in dp[0], which is the minimum length of the resulting string after applying all possible operations.

